nc workspace\" action\n- part of branch/PR publish\n- best-effort background sync for opted-in projects\n\nThat policy should live above `but-agentlog`; the crate should provide a small\nsync primitive and clear result reporting.\n\n## Failure Handling\n\nFor the explicit command:\n\n- missing GitMeta remote should fail clearly\n- fetch/materialize failure should fail the command\n- push non-fast-forward should retry after fetch/materialize/re-serialize\n- repeated push failure should fail clearly\n- no remote data and no local changes should succeed with an up-to-date message\n\nFor future integration with normal GitButler push/fetch flows, the product needs\nto decide whether metadata sync failure blocks code sync or is reported as a\nrecoverable warning.\n\n## Decided POC Choices\n\n- `but agentlog sync` is a full bidirectional sync command.\n- Do not add `--push-only` or `--pull-only` until there is a concrete need.\n- If `--remote` is omitted, use `origin`.\n- The key scope/ref suffix should match the local GitMeta name for agentlog.\n- Keep the implementation as normal GitMeta exchange: serialize, fetch,\n  materialize, and push. Do not add custom backend ingestion or product-specific\n  sharing behavior for the POC.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T16:48:51.228Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}